      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs (hemolysis index) directly correspond to the clinical decision QoIs; surrogate QoIs justified if direct measurement is infeasible.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) as a surrogate for the modified index of hemolysis (MIH) used in the COU. The mapping between NIH and MIH is not formally justified for the VAD flow regime."
    },
    {
